Into the Spider-Verse looks soooo good. 
Also, I can't believe I haven't said this yet, but I'm so proud of Sony for making a...
body:
Into the Spider-Verse looks soooo good.

Also, I can’t believe I haven’t said this yet, but I’m so proud of Sony for making a Miles Morales movie. Every child deserves to feel represented, and superheroes are for everyone, and Miles Morales makes superheroes so much more relatable for so many more people.

Publisher: Marvel 
Abilities: Superhuman strength, speed, agility, reflexes, durability, and hearing; Enhanced...
body:
Hispanic Heritage Month Spotlight: Spider-Man 2099

Miguel O'Hara

Publisher: Marvel

Abilities: Superhuman strength, speed, agility, reflexes, durability, and hearing; Enhanced healing and health; Enhanced vision (telescopic and night-vision); Genius-level intelligence; Talons on fingers and toes that enable wall-crawling, act as weapons, and can be folded down; Organic webbing from forearms; Temporary-paralysis venom from fangs; Wears indestructible costume of unstable molecule fabric with air-foil that allows gliding

Source: wiki

Miguel O'Hara is a brilliant geneticist living in New York in the year 2099 A.D. who is attempting to recreate the abilities of the original Spider-Man.  He suffers a related accident that causes half his DNA to be re-written with a spider’s genetic code. O'Hara is the first Latino character to assume the identity of Spider-Man
